&gt; I want to move my HTML player a little bit down

To move any element further down from where it would normally appear in the document flow, you can use a number of approaches:

#Approach #1: Vertical Translation

    transform: translateY(24px);

The `transform: translateY()` style states how far down from normal position in the document flow you want the element to appear. ie. if you only declared `transform: translateY(0)` the element would appear in exactly the same position as it would normally appear in the document flow.

**Working Example:**

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;








&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    div {
      display: inline-block;
      width: 100px;
      height: 100px;
      margin: 0 12px;
      text-align: center;
      color: rgb(255, 255, 255);
      background-color: rgb(255, 0, 0);
    }

    div:nth-of-type(2) {
      transform: translateY(0);
    }

    div:nth-of-type(3) {
      transform: translateY(24px);
    }

    div:nth-of-type(4) {
      transform: translateY(72px);
    }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

#Approach #2: Relative Positioning

    position: relative;
    top: 24px;

The `top` style states how far down from normal position in the document flow you want the element to appear. ie. if you only declared `top: 0` the element would appear in exactly the same position as it would normally appear in the document flow.

**Working Example:**

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    div {
      display: inline-block;
      width: 100px;
      height: 100px;
      margin: 0 12px;
      text-align: center;
      color: rgb(255, 255, 255);
      background-color: rgb(255, 0, 0);
    }

    div:nth-of-type(2) {
      position: relative;
      top: 0;
    }

    div:nth-of-type(3) {
      position: relative;
      top: 24px;
    }

    div:nth-of-type(4) {
      position: relative;
      top: 72px;
    }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
